## Purpose

The `Makefile` is the human-friendly entrypoint that wraps `scripts/stack.sh` with a docker-compose-like interface.

## Conventions

- Keep the positional-arg interface stable:
  - `make <cmd> <stack> [-- <args...>]`
- Make targets should delegate to `bash scripts/stack.sh ...` rather than duplicating logic.
- Keep `help` output up to date when adding/removing commands.
- Avoid targets that implicitly destroy data (volumes) without an explicit, documented opt-in flag.

## Path drift

If you change stack root layout (e.g. migrate between `stacks/` and legacy `docker/stacks/`), update `scripts/stack.sh` first and keep Makefile help text consistent with reality.
